            </para>
          </subprov>
        </prov.body>
      </prov>
      <prov id="DLM1956415" irdnumbering="no" skeleton="no" toc="yes">
        <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">8</label>
        <heading>How a school defines its home zone</heading>
        <prov.body>
          <subprov skeleton="no">
            <label auto.number="yes" denominator="yes"/>
            <para>
              <text>Section 11E(2)(c) is amended by omitting <amend.in quote="1">which</amend.in> and substituting <amend.in quote="1">that</amend.in>.</text>
            </para>
          </subprov>
        </prov.body>
      </prov>
      <prov id="DLM1956416" irdnumbering="no" skeleton="no" toc="yes">
        <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">9</label>
        <heading>Amendment of enrolment scheme</heading>
        <prov.body>
          <subprov skeleton="no">
            <label auto.number="yes" denominator="yes"/>
            <para>
              <text>Section 11M(3) is amended by omitting <amend.in quote="1">enrolment scheme, in order</amend.in> and substituting <amend.in quote="1">enrolment scheme in order</amend.in>. </text>
            </para>
          </subprov>
        </prov.body>
      </prov>
      <prov id="DLM1956417" irdnumbering="no" skeleton="no" toc="yes">
        <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">10</label>
        <heading>Obligation to report to Parliament on enrolment schemes</heading>
        <prov.body>
          <subprov skeleton="no">
            <label auto.number="yes" denominator="yes"/>
            <para>
              <text>Section 11Q(1) is amended by omitting <amend.in quote="1">sector which</amend.in> and substituting <amend.in quote="1">sector that</amend.in>.</text>
            </para>
          </subprov>
        </prov.body>
      </prov>
